<span id="freeTextContainer14843540662027500302">I couldn’t put it down, this book hits too close to reality. Mark M Bello makes an amazing job with two of the most critical topics in 2020, gun control and bullying; the story starts with Kevin Burns, a boy who has had enough of bullying; and in an act of desperation commits acts of violence.<br/><br/>And this time the hero once again is the amazing Zack Blake, who is looking for the answers and reasons why Kevin Burns might commit such actions. The story manages to understand the victims, the perpetrato</span>
  <span id="freeText14843540662027500302" style="display:none">I couldn’t put it down, this book hits too close to reality. Mark M Bello makes an amazing job with two of the most critical topics in 2020, gun control and bullying; the story starts with Kevin Burns, a boy who has had enough of bullying; and in an act of desperation commits acts of violence.<br /><br />And this time the hero once again is the amazing Zack Blake, who is looking for the answers and reasons why Kevin Burns might commit such actions. The story manages to understand the victims, the perpetrator and all the reasons behind these actions and the way each of the characters understand the situation.<br /><br />Fiction but a great story that puts on stand the true reasons of gun control, bullying and the social connection that exists as a community.</span>
