<div id="review_3473440547" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3473440547" />
    <a title="Pallavi Sareen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22595830-pallavi-sareen"><img alt="Pallavi Sareen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1473247887p2/22595830.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3473440547?book_show_action=true">Aug 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pallavi Sareen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pallavi Sareen" href="/user/show/22595830-pallavi-sareen">Pallavi Sareen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3473440547" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9869216890542848333">Even though I do love to read books on sensitive topics, it is very rare to come across such books especially in the fiction genre. The California shooting shook everyone to the core. Shooting, inside a school, a place which we often associate as a safe space for learning and personality development can be beyond traumatic. Mark M. Bello deals with this theme in his book Betrayal High. The book delves into the story of a school shooting in Michigan as told from different point of views to unders</span>
  <span id="freeText9869216890542848333" style="display:none">Even though I do love to read books on sensitive topics, it is very rare to come across such books especially in the fiction genre. The California shooting shook everyone to the core. Shooting, inside a school, a place which we often associate as a safe space for learning and personality development can be beyond traumatic. Mark M. Bello deals with this theme in his book Betrayal High. The book delves into the story of a school shooting in Michigan as told from different point of views to understand it. It goes beyond one-dimensional news stories, as the creative freedom of novels allows and creates the same atmosphere for the reader. <br /><br />I must say, it was terrifying. <br /><br />The initial chapters which introduced us to the various characters Kevin and Kenny had such different narration which immediately allowed the reader to understand the difference between a chaotic mind that had too much going on and a sane one. But I didn't like the fact that the book began immediately with the action. I would rather understand the characters beforehand and get a glimpse of the circumstances that led up to it. But what it does deal with is the aftermath, which is no less consequential. The trauma that such an incident leaves on the mind of everyone, even the ones not directly impacted is immeasurable. I saw Kenny struggle with his mental health despite being the hero of the situation and it felt so realistic. <br /><br /><i>“Kevin did not believe he was going to survive the shooting, did he?”<br />“No, he didn’t. He was shocked he survived. He planned to use a homemade bomb and two powerful automatic weapons to kill as many ‘bullies,’ as he refers to his victims, as he could. </i><br /><br />The legal battle is all the more exhausting to read, as they are exhausting to experience but at no point in the book did I feel like it wasn't worth it. Given the experience I had, I would love to read more book by Mark. So, I would definitely recommend picking this up. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9869216890542848333" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


