<div id="review_3482956337" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3482956337" />
    <a title="Sizarifalina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3712998-sizarifalina"><img alt="Sizarifalina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1323688744p2/3712998.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3482956337?book_show_action=true">Aug 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sizarifalina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sizarifalina" href="/user/show/3712998-sizarifalina">Sizarifalina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3482956337" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15310414993505083268">We cannot blame a person for a mass shooting. The whole community and the country need to take responsibility when one occurs. This is portrayed in Betrayal High. From this book I read about stories on how each and everyone who were involved in the mass shooting were trying their best to not take the blame and would do anything to blame others. No doubt that Betrayal High is fiction, but the author wrote it like it was a documentary based on true events. It was both entertaining and informative </span>
  <span id="freeText15310414993505083268" style="display:none">We cannot blame a person for a mass shooting. The whole community and the country need to take responsibility when one occurs. This is portrayed in Betrayal High. From this book I read about stories on how each and everyone who were involved in the mass shooting were trying their best to not take the blame and would do anything to blame others. No doubt that Betrayal High is fiction, but the author wrote it like it was a documentary based on true events. It was both entertaining and informative for me as I am from Malaysia. Owning a personal gun is illegal here. So there are near to zero mass shootings in schools. From this book I learned a lot about how a country takes mass shootings as a big problem or not. They relate it to mental illnesses. As a person with mental illnesses I can understand why these two are related. It is like a suicidal person with access to loads of psychiatric meds. Those meds are like weapons. The difference is that the meds would only harm the suicidal person but the weapons kill others. I could see how the company that manufactured the weapons, the school , the parents of the students who died, the parents of the shooter , the shooter’s father ...(the list goes on) are fighting for their rights and also discussing on how to tackle the issues in the book. It saddens me when I read how some of them can be very blunt and selfish. Bullying was also mentioned in the book. It could lead to mental health issues then later to a mass shooting. <br />Kevin , the shooter has a lot of reasons to be angry which lead him to do what he did. This shows clearly that mental health is extreamely important especially in the 21st Century where everyone is judged no matter who they are. Being judged is extreamely painful and exhausting when one is just a teenager like Kevin - the odd one out! </span>
  <a data-text-id="15310414993505083268" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


