<div id="review_3433211550" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3433211550" />
    <a title="Kimberly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8091824-kimberly"><img alt="Kimberly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1504545322p2/8091824.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3433211550?book_show_action=true">Jul 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kimberly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kimberly" href="/user/show/8091824-kimberly">Kimberly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3433211550" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14412025352735146784">Betrayal High by Mark M. Bello is the 5th in the Zach Blake series. While I have not read the first 4, I did not have any issues reading this one as a stand alone. <br/><br/>A young man living with parents that pay no attention to him, a school where he doesn&apos;t fit in, and tormented by bullies. All leading to a school shooting that could have possibly been avoid if someone just cared enough. <br/><br/>I enjoyed reading this book, although it was less about the high school shooting (maybe about 1/3 of the book) and </span>
  <span id="freeText14412025352735146784" style="display:none">Betrayal High by Mark M. Bello is the 5th in the Zach Blake series. While I have not read the first 4, I did not have any issues reading this one as a stand alone. <br /><br />A young man living with parents that pay no attention to him, a school where he doesn't fit in, and tormented by bullies. All leading to a school shooting that could have possibly been avoid if someone just cared enough. <br /><br />I enjoyed reading this book, although it was less about the high school shooting (maybe about 1/3 of the book) and more about gun laws and going after the gun company and other bad people. I also found 2 new quotes that I love. I am definitely going to have catch up with the series, and am looking forward to the next one.<br /><br />"There is no love without forgiveness and there is no forgiveness without love." - Bryant McGill<br /><br />"When you hold resentment toward another, you are bound to that person or condition by an emotional link that is far stronger than steel. Forgiveness is the only way to dissolve that link and get free." - Catherine Ponder<br /><br />Thank you to BookSirens for the free digital ARC in exchange for an honest and voluntary review. All opinions are my own.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14412025352735146784" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
