        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3434089835" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10575881100911135849">Betrayal High is the fifth book in the Zachary Blake Legal Thrillers, and Mark M. Bello again writes about topics that hit close to home. Kenny Tracey faces someone more harmful than the priest that abused him, but a fellow student who’s had enough and settles the school bullying with firearms. Out of fear for his son and a call for justice, Zack Blake takes on the big boys. Clare Gibson from the FBI and the Private Investigator Micah Love is hunting for pieces to the puzzle of who is involved i</span>
  <span id="freeText10575881100911135849" style="display:none">Betrayal High is the fifth book in the Zachary Blake Legal Thrillers, and Mark M. Bello again writes about topics that hit close to home. Kenny Tracey faces someone more harmful than the priest that abused him, but a fellow student who’s had enough and settles the school bullying with firearms. Out of fear for his son and a call for justice, Zack Blake takes on the big boys. Clare Gibson from the FBI and the Private Investigator Micah Love is hunting for pieces to the puzzle of who is involved in a murder. Will they find the clues needed to discover who was behind hiring the assassin who had Kenny in his cross hairs?<br /> <br />I love reading Mark M. Bello’s novels. He isn’t afraid to hit subjects that are uncomfortable. I don’t always like the stand that Zack takes. In this novel, I wished the side effects of bullying and neglect were pushed more, but that wasn’t the point of this novel. Overall, you will not find a legal thriller that is more intense and professional than by Bello. I am anticipating the next in this series, Supreme Betrayal.  </span>
