        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3494503078" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17249779465464886759">Betrayal High is Mark M. Bello’s fifth book in his Zachary Blake Betrayal series. The opening of the story dives right into the mind of a bullied high school student who has had enough. Kevin Burns has decided to end the bullying once and for all at any cost. The day he enters his high school armed and ready to kill using guns from his father’s gun cabinet has a lasting impact on the residents of Bloomfield, Michigan. <br/><br/>Evil thoughts are ruling Kevin’s mind as he shoots his bullies and others who </span>
  <span id="freeText17249779465464886759" style="display:none">Betrayal High is Mark M. Bello’s fifth book in his Zachary Blake Betrayal series. The opening of the story dives right into the mind of a bullied high school student who has had enough. Kevin Burns has decided to end the bullying once and for all at any cost. The day he enters his high school armed and ready to kill using guns from his father’s gun cabinet has a lasting impact on the residents of Bloomfield, Michigan. <br /><br />Evil thoughts are ruling Kevin’s mind as he shoots his bullies and others who just happen to be in his pathway. Zachary Blake’s two stepsons attend the same high school and are in separate areas of the building as Kevin commits his crime. The oldest son, Kenny is shot just before law enforcement arrives. When Zach and the boys’ mother get the news, Zach becomes angry and the boy’s mother is distraught. Quickly going into lawyer mode, Zachary Blake wants answers. While all Kevin really wants is to teach people about how much bullying hurts emotionally and physically. <br /><br />Civil justice attorney Zachary Blake is soon engaged to represent Kenny and the families of the people Kevin killed and injured with a major lawsuit against the school department, the gun manufacturer, gun dealers, and Kevin’s parents for their neglect. As more details emerge events occur that reveal pure evil from characters who are greedy, narcissistic, and powerful that will go to no end to hide their misdeeds including the fictional president, Ronald John.<br /><br />As always, Bello reflects on real events in his stories making them relatable and thought-provoking. This story also becomes a testament to the younger generation becoming involved in change for the better good of this country. When you finish reading Betrayal High, I guarantee that you will be looking forward to reading the sixth book in this series. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17249779465464886759" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


