<div id="review_3457229945" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3457229945" />
    <a title="Jessica Bone" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/69519751-jessica-bone"><img alt="Jessica Bone" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509540250p2/69519751.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3457229945?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica Bone" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica Bone" href="/user/show/69519751-jessica-bone">Jessica Bone</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3457229945" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7440515409708472846">Kenny Tracey finds himself in the spotlight once again when a fellow classmate Kevin Burns walks into their high school and shoots and kills nine students and teachers and injured many more to include Kenny. Kenny was shot while stopping Kevin before he could get to his AK47. Kenny stepdad, Zack Blake will stop at nothing to find justice and change the rules about gun safety. Has Mr. Blake finally picked a battle he can not win and as he takes on the whole lot to include changing laws, banning g</span>
  <span id="freeText7440515409708472846" style="display:none">Kenny Tracey finds himself in the spotlight once again when a fellow classmate Kevin Burns walks into their high school and shoots and kills nine students and teachers and injured many more to include Kenny. Kenny was shot while stopping Kevin before he could get to his AK47. Kenny stepdad, Zack Blake will stop at nothing to find justice and change the rules about gun safety. Has Mr. Blake finally picked a battle he can not win and as he takes on the whole lot to include changing laws, banning guns, and the NRA.<br /><br />Mark M. Bello has hit it out of the park with his latest legal thriller Betrayal HIgh. I honestly had me in the first chapter and the face he allowed the character, Kevin, to survive the stand-off at the school as a complete bonus. You will find this to be easy to read the book, but it does cover some very hard truths. The fact he covers the death of children, school shootings, gun control, and the law in the first four chapters lets you know this is an emotionally charged book and is not for children. I did find parts of the story hard to read. The writing is well done and I can say nothing negative of the story-line. I just found myself crying a lot because of the emotional connection you feel for the characters. I actually even felt for the shooter Kevin,  everyone could see needed help and was offered none by anyone. A good book would be enjoyed by fellow legal thriller fans. Like I said before not an all age definitely adult level.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7440515409708472846" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
