        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3473295978" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15520723759506794046">Zachery Blake is back. This time, he plays second fiddle to his oldest son, Kenny. Kenny and Jake, the younger son, are both in high school. High school, for most people, is not the funnest place to be at times. <br/><br/><br/>For their friend, Kevin, high school was akin to hell on earth. One fine day, Kevin decides that enough is enough and he is going to a little housekeeping. After a little training, he heads to school and kills nine people. Kevin&apos;s plan is rather interrupted when Kenny makes his move, get</span>
  <span id="freeText15520723759506794046" style="display:none">Zachery Blake is back. This time, he plays second fiddle to his oldest son, Kenny. Kenny and Jake, the younger son, are both in high school. High school, for most people, is not the funnest place to be at times. <br /><br /><br />For their friend, Kevin, high school was akin to hell on earth. One fine day, Kevin decides that enough is enough and he is going to a little housekeeping. After a little training, he heads to school and kills nine people. Kevin's plan is rather interrupted when Kenny makes his move, getting shot in the process. This kind of changes the end result and Kevin ends up in jail.<br /><br /><br />Zachery Blake then takes centre stage as he proceeds to prosecute Kevin for his conduct. This is only the first layer to peel aside. Zach also intends to prosecute the gun company as well. Only when he begins to dig deeper does he realise how deep the rabbit hole really goes. It also exposes him and his family to some very dangerous and motivated enemies who would like to clean up a few loose ends. <br /><br /><br />Mr. Bello, in his fifth Zachery Blake novel, delivers a wonderful combination of high school activism and danger, political intrigue and courtroom drama. The story is well conceived, imbued with reality and carries through to a satisfying conclusion. It is sadly rather relevant in today's day and age. At least in this story, you know justice will prevail in the end. <br /><br /><br />I am volunteering a review for the benefit of others."</span>
  <a data-text-id="15520723759506794046" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
