        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3529246573" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11092981265751995710">The cover and title caught attracted me initially and I wanted to read the book. This is a subject that lots of people wonder about. When there are mass shootings in schools the first thing that comes to mind is &quot;WHY&quot;? The dialogue going on in Kevin&apos;s mind explains the why and how devastating bullying is and what damage it can do to an individual experiencing it. I loved the character Kenny too, the way he had survived bullying and other traumas but came back to try and stop the shooter becoming</span>
  <span id="freeText11092981265751995710" style="display:none">The cover and title caught attracted me initially and I wanted to read the book. This is a subject that lots of people wonder about. When there are mass shootings in schools the first thing that comes to mind is "WHY"? The dialogue going on in Kevin's mind explains the why and how devastating bullying is and what damage it can do to an individual experiencing it. I loved the character Kenny too, the way he had survived bullying and other traumas but came back to try and stop the shooter becoming the hero instead of a victim. Loved the story and will definitely read other stories from this author.</span>
