<span id="freeTextContainer10224279215306440982">2020, Kevin Burns is all alone in the house. <br/>Bloomfield, MI (Oakland County). Susan Burns (wife/mother) left for work, who knows where Charles Burns (husband/father) is.<br/>The gun cabinet keys are in Charles’ cigar box.<br/>That AK47 &amp; the Luger look great.<br/><br/>The AK47 is shoulder-strapped to his body, &amp; the Luger is in his right hand.<br/>110 S. classroom empty. 112 S. classroom is also empty.<br/>Kevin spies Drew coming down the hallway. <br/>BANG! BANG!<br/>Mr. Fletcher (shop teacher).<br/>BANG! BANG!<br/>Marwin Singleton (A/A) died </span>
  <span id="freeText10224279215306440982" style="display:none">2020, Kevin Burns is all alone in the house. <br />Bloomfield, MI (Oakland County). Susan Burns (wife/mother) left for work, who knows where Charles Burns (husband/father) is.<br />The gun cabinet keys are in Charles’ cigar box.<br />That AK47 &amp; the Luger look great.<br /><br />The AK47 is shoulder-strapped to his body, &amp; the Luger is in his right hand.<br />110 S. classroom empty. 112 S. classroom is also empty.<br />Kevin spies Drew coming down the hallway. <br />BANG! BANG!<br />Mr. Fletcher (shop teacher).<br />BANG! BANG!<br />Marwin Singleton (A/A) died immediately, &amp; Sam Bolton (A/A) died in-route to St. Joseph’s Hospital.<br />Mrs. Culpepper (art teacher) will not teach again. The 6 art students were locked in the storage room. <br />Jake &amp; 15 other students are listening to Mrs. Clarke (English teacher). <br />Jake texted Kenny.<br />Bloomfield HS central lobby. Kevin sets the timer on the bomb for 4 minutes. <br />2 teachers &amp; 3 students are gunned down.<br />Kevin sees Kenny coming toward him &amp; hoist the AK47 &amp; fires, as Kenny slams into him full force the 2 boys tumble to the ground.<br />Officer Alvarez (Bloomfield HS Security guard) &amp; the Bloomfield PD SWAT team intervene. <br />BOOM!<br /><br />The public would hear the Barrington Arms Corporation side of the story right away.<br />Devon Harlan (ViewPoint TV news anchor host) was interviewing live Bloomfield HS students: Kenny Tracey, Alex Pratt, Jacqueline Corey, Emma Cohen, &amp; Cameron Casey who have organized a political action group called the First Time Voters of America FTVA.<br />Jennifer was on the Bloomfield PTA board. Keri Levin (PTA president) subject matter was student safety.<br />Civil trial.<br />Plaintiff: Zachary “Zack” Blake (husband/father, attorney) Bloomfield HS district would like the matter settled out of court. <br />Defense: Roland “Rollie” Barrington III (Barrington Arms Corp. CEO); Jules Grimes (Grimes, Rhodes &amp; Burke Sr. partner) represents Barrington Arms &amp; various gun sellers; &amp; Burl Tyner (Michwide homeowners insurance attorney).<br />Jules could hope for a facilitative mediation.<br />Orchard Lake Country Club (West Shore Dr.) W. Bloomfield township, Oakland County MI. Zack agrees to meet with Jules. <br />An offer was made. <br />Then came a counteroffer: Jules &amp; the defendants are now offering binding arbitration &amp; minimum-maximum settlement terms in exchange for a dismissal of the lawsuit &amp; partial confidentiality. <br />Barry Frazier is the sole mediator-facilitator-arbitrator.<br /><br />The cases of the Bloomfield School Shooting victims v. Kevin, Charles and Susan Burns, Bloomfield Schools, Roland Barrington, and Barrington Arms are officially over.<br />Will the final offer be accepted by the other parties in behalf of Zack? <br />Criminal trial. <br />All rise. The District Court of Oakland County is now in session, The Honorable Judge Hugo Selik<br />is presiding. <br />State v Burns.<br />Prosecution: ADA Karen Sprague <br />Defense: Charles “Charlie” Barnes would be representing Kevin Burns (21, autism spectrum D/O).<br />Susan Burns (wife/mother) &amp; Charles Burns (45, husband/father) are there also. <br />Kevin Burns would be required to plead guilty to 9 counts of 1st &amp; 2nd degree murder.<br />The charges could be reduced to voluntary manslaughter (15 yrs. consecutively) &amp; multiple counts of assault with intent to kill.<br />ADA Karen Sprague 1st witness is Dr. Elliot Spitz (psychiatrist, MD).<br />What was the final verdict? <br /><br />BOOM!<br />Cameron had been killed. <br />FBI SA Clare Gibson (Detroit) &amp; Detective Billy Ellington (Michigan PD) have been assigned to the bombing case. <br />Detective Ellington met/gave Zack, &amp; PI Micah Love (Love Investigations) an update.<br />Roland is President Ronald John’s single largest contributor to his campaign trail.<br />Will FBI SA Gibson &amp; the ATF be able to file another criminal case on Roland Barrington, and Barrington Arms? <br /><br />I do not receive any type of compensation for reading &amp; reviewing free books from publishers &amp; authors. Therefore, I am under no obligation to write a positive review, only an honest one. <br /><br />Warning: This book contains descriptive accounts of extremely graphic adult content, violence, or expletive language &amp;/or uncensored explicit material (racism, minor verbally, psychologically, emotionally physically abuse) which is only suitable for mature readers. It may be offensive or have potential adverse psychological effects on the reader. If you are especially sensitive to this type of material, it is strongly advised not to read any further.<br /><br />An awesome book cover, great font &amp; writing style. A very professionally written Legal Thriller book. It was extremely easy for me to read/follow from start/finish &amp; never a dull moment. There were no grammar/typo errors, nor any repetitive or out of line sequence sentences. Lots of exciting scenarios, with several twists/turns &amp; a huge description list of unique characters, settings, facts etc. to keep track of. This could also make another great Legal Thriller movie, or better yet a mini TV series. There is no doubt in my mind this is an extremely easy rating of 5 stars. <br /><br />Thank you for the free author; 8Grand Publications; Goodreads; MakingConnections; Making Connections discussion group talk; PDF book. <br />Tony Parsons MSW (Washburn)<br /></span>
