<div id="review_3481925662" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3481925662" />
    <a title="Melissa Ammons" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68967103-melissa-ammons"><img alt="Melissa Ammons" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498623735p2/68967103.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3481925662?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melissa Ammons" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melissa Ammons" href="/user/show/68967103-melissa-ammons">Melissa Ammons</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3481925662" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1552682751944794869">I am putting a disclaimer on this book that it could potentially contain triggers, especially for those folks who have been bullied. I think this book should be recommended reading for young people. This book tackles a big topic - that of bullying. It tells the story from the perspective of a young man who was bullied and the consequences his &quot;abuse&quot; had on his life, and touches on the relationship he had with his family. It tells the story of a strong family relationship, from the perspective o</span>
  <span id="freeText1552682751944794869" style="display:none">I am putting a disclaimer on this book that it could potentially contain triggers, especially for those folks who have been bullied. I think this book should be recommended reading for young people. This book tackles a big topic - that of bullying. It tells the story from the perspective of a young man who was bullied and the consequences his "abuse" had on his life, and touches on the relationship he had with his family. It tells the story of a strong family relationship, from the perspective of the lawyer who handled the case. While some parts of this book are quite "dry and boring," I think the story in its entirety comes together in the end. As a society, I think we need to do more to stop and somehow learn to prevent bullying and the consequences it can have. It is deep reading for sure. I commend Mr. Bello for tackling such a tough subject. (As a member of Book Sirens, I received a free advance review copy and am leaving this review voluntarily.)</span>
  <a data-text-id="1552682751944794869" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
