    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3613804678" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3613804678" />
    <a title="Sol Tyty" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/111899066-sol-tyty"><img alt="Sol Tyty" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1586363569p2/111899066.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3613804678?book_show_action=true">Oct 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sol Tyty" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sol Tyty" href="/user/show/111899066-sol-tyty">Sol Tyty</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3613804678" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16524362614564935326">Wow, what a heart-stopping fifth installment of the Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Series! Trial lawyer, Zachary Blake, has performed some fascinating investigations on the Church and on the death of a black man in Michigan in previous books on this series. This time, he appears on scene again, but to bring relief to families and justice to a whole community which has undergone a terrible bloody episode perpetuated by a young character called Kevin Burns. Tired of being bullied, Burns decides to p</span>
  <span id="freeText16524362614564935326" style="display:none">Wow, what a heart-stopping fifth installment of the Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Series! Trial lawyer, Zachary Blake, has performed some fascinating investigations on the Church and on the death of a black man in Michigan in previous books on this series. This time, he appears on scene again, but to bring relief to families and justice to a whole community which has undergone a terrible bloody episode perpetuated by a young character called Kevin Burns. Tired of being bullied, Burns decides to pull the trigger of his father’s gun at school and leaves everyone asking themselves “why?”. <br />I must admit I love books written in the form of dialogues, and this is actually the way Mark Bello has decided to pen Betrayal High. So, I could not help being hooked right from the very first page. By resorting to such a touchy theme as bullying and by choosing a simple narrative style, Bello has been able to develop a fiction which seems to be a real-life story due to the contemporary content of its thirty four chapters. He has employed the third person singular and has proven that his writing skill is on point. <br />Another important ingredient of this book are the characters. Identifying with the characters is usually one of the reasons why readers love certain books more than others. In this particular case, the main characters and the supporting ones develop like people do in real life and that is one of the reasons why the story is so captivating. <br />Betrayal High is directed to an adult audience, but I believe young adults and adolescents can also enjoy this gem as much as I did. It teaches lessons and allows readers to look at a matter which is, unfortunately, always in vogue from another perspective. <br />Even though this tale belongs to a series, the plot is so well-constructed that it can be read as a standalone. It is definitely an entertaining read that should not be missed! </span>
  <a data-text-id="16524362614564935326" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


