<div id="review_3614099901" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3614099901" />
    <a title="Ivana S." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54368729-ivana-s"><img alt="Ivana S." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1595544859p2/54368729.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3614099901?book_show_action=true">Oct 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ivana S." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ivana S." href="/user/show/54368729-ivana-s">Ivana S.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3614099901" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5638846411513539480">This is a breathtaking and thought-provoking novel! “Betrayal High” written by Mark M. Bello is a book that contains thirty-four chapters full of action and tension. <br/><br/>The story takes place in Michigan. It seems like a “normal” high school day for everyone but Kevin Burns, who has been subject of cruel school bullying, has other plans: he is carrying a handgun in one hand, a AK47 over his shoulder and a pressure bomb to take over all the bullies. Kenny Tracey, who is in his senior year, is a good </span>
  <span id="freeText5638846411513539480" style="display:none">This is a breathtaking and thought-provoking novel! “Betrayal High” written by Mark M. Bello is a book that contains thirty-four chapters full of action and tension. <br /><br />The story takes place in Michigan. It seems like a “normal” high school day for everyone but Kevin Burns, who has been subject of cruel school bullying, has other plans: he is carrying a handgun in one hand, a AK47 over his shoulder and a pressure bomb to take over all the bullies. Kenny Tracey, who is in his senior year, is a good and loyal friend and big brother. He had a tough life because his father passed away when he and his brother were little kids. Kenny knows he has to do something, so he tries to take Kevin’s weapons and achieves to stop him. Zachary Blake, Kenny’s step-dad, is a successful lawyer who is convinced to file a lawsuit to everyone involved in this case. Is he going to make it? <br /><br />The suspenseful elements of the plot of this book kept me engaged from the start of the book. Bellos’s writing style is a skill to be appreciated as the sentences are well crafted and enjoyable to read. In fact, he drops significant indicators that keep the suspense alive by referring to a back story. He strings past with present and gives the reader a visual inventory to decipher the tension. <br /><br />I think that the characters are perfectly well-drawn; they are normal people who have been through a lot and that makes it easy to emphasize with them. You can take notice of the mental, spiritual and emotional side of them. <br /><br />All in all, what struck me was the subject of the novel because it is something that happens nowadays all over the world. Teenagers are bullying targets and think that holding guns is the only way to take revenge for themselves. As a primary school teacher I’m very worried about this. I would recommend this book to adults but also to teens because everyone will find something to appreciate. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5638846411513539480" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


